00:14:48.110 --> 00:14:54.760
So v1 was equal to the vector
ac, and v2 is equal

00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:57.600
to the vector bd.

00:14:57.600 --> 00:14:59.790
So what is v1 dot v1?

00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:08.750
That is equal to a dot
a, a times a, a

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:11.020
squared plus c squared.

00:15:11.020 --> 00:15:12.990
That's this, right there.

00:15:12.990 --> 00:15:14.800
And that's what? v2 dot v2.

00:15:14.800 --> 00:15:19.740
So we're going to have
that times v2 dot v2.

00:15:19.740 --> 00:15:25.030
v2 dot v2 is v squared
plus d squared.

00:15:25.030 --> 00:15:30.450
And then we're going to have
minus v2 dot v1 squared.

00:15:30.450 --> 00:15:34.080
So what's v2 dot v1?

00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:38.590
It's b times a, plus d times c,
or a times b plus -- we're

00:15:38.590 --> 00:15:39.850
just dotting these two guys.

00:15:39.850 --> 00:15:46.600
So it's ab plus cd, and then
we're squaring it.

00:15:46.600 --> 00:15:48.910
And let's see what this
simplifies to.

00:15:48.910 --> 00:15:51.630
Hopefully it simplifies
to something.

00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:53.050
Let me switch colors.

00:15:53.050 --> 00:15:55.550
So if we just multiply this
out, let me write it here.

00:15:55.550 --> 00:15:59.185
Our area squared is equal to
a squared times b squared.

00:16:01.930 --> 00:16:08.150
a squared times d squared,
plus c squared times b

00:16:08.150 --> 00:16:13.670
squared, plus c squared
times d squared.

00:16:17.350 --> 00:16:21.220
And then minus this
guy squared.

00:16:21.220 --> 00:16:22.960
What is that going
to be equal to?

00:16:22.960 --> 00:16:26.620
ab squared is a squared,
b squared.

00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:29.650
And then I'm going to multiply
these guys times each other

00:16:29.650 --> 00:16:35.750
twice, so that's going
to be plus 2abcd.

00:16:35.750 --> 00:16:40.020
And then you're going to have
a plus c squared, d squared.

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:42.260
I just foiled this out, that's
the best way you

00:16:42.260 --> 00:16:44.010
could think about it.

00:16:44.010 --> 00:16:47.920
And then, if I distribute this
negative sign, what do I have?

00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:49.230
Let me rewrite everything.

00:16:49.230 --> 00:16:53.380
It's equal to a squared b
squared, plus a squared d

00:16:53.380 --> 00:16:59.100
squared, plus c squared b
squared, plus c squared d

00:16:59.100 --> 00:17:08.060
squared, minus a squared b
squared, minus 2abcd, minus c

00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:09.200
squared, d squared.

00:17:09.200 --> 00:17:11.920
All I did is, I distributed
the minus sign.

00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:14.960
Now it looks like some things
will simplify nicely.

00:17:14.960 --> 00:17:17.550
And now remember, all this is
equal to our area squared.

00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:21.180
We have a ab squared, we have
a minus ab squared.

00:17:21.180 --> 00:17:22.589
They cancel out.

00:17:22.589 --> 00:17:27.130
We have a minus cd squared
and a cd squared,

00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:28.650
so they cancel out.

00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:32.100
So all we're left with is that
the area of our parallelogram

00:17:32.100 --> 00:17:45.490
squared is equal to a squared
d squared minus 2abcd plus c

00:17:45.490 --> 00:17:47.740
squared b squared.

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:55.910
Now this might look a little bit
bizarre to you, but if you

00:17:55.910 --> 00:17:59.210
made a substitution right here,
if you said that x is

00:17:59.210 --> 00:18:04.540
equal to ad, and if you said y
is equal to cb, then what does

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:06.730
this become?

00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:10.220
This is equal to x
squared minus 2

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:14.180
times xy plus y squared.

00:18:14.180 --> 00:18:14.750
Right?

00:18:14.750 --> 00:18:15.740
Hopefully you recognize this.

00:18:15.740 --> 00:18:20.610
And this is just the same thing
as x minus y squared.

00:18:20.610 --> 00:18:23.580
So, if this is our substitutions
we made-- I did

00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:26.940
this just so you can visualize
this a little bit better.

00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:32.980
So we have our area squared is
equal to x minus y squared or

00:18:32.980 --> 00:18:39.640
ad minus cb, or let me
write it, bc squared.

00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:43.960
That's what the area of our
parallelogram squared is.

00:18:43.960 --> 00:18:46.540
And if you don't quite
understand what I did here, I

00:18:46.540 --> 00:18:47.890
just made these substitutions
so you can

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:49.080
recognize it better.

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:51.010
But just understand that this
is the same thing as this.

00:18:51.010 --> 00:18:54.100
If you want, you can just
multiply this guy out and

00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:55.670
you'll get that right there.

00:18:55.670 --> 00:18:58.650
But what is this?

00:18:58.650 --> 00:19:00.700
What is this thing right here?

00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:02.250
It's the determinant.

00:19:02.250 --> 00:19:05.470
This is the determinant of
our original matrix.

00:19:09.380 --> 00:19:12.710
Well, I called that matrix A
and then I used A again for

00:19:12.710 --> 00:19:15.460
area, so let me write
it this way.

00:19:15.460 --> 00:19:19.880
Area squared -- let me
write it like this.

00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:27.870
Area squared is equal to
ad minus bc squared.

00:19:27.870 --> 00:19:31.940
So this is area, these
A's are all area.

00:19:31.940 --> 00:19:32.940
But what is this?

00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:34.770
This is the determinant
of my matrix.

00:19:34.770 --> 00:19:43.050
That is the determinant of my
matrix A, my original matrix

00:19:43.050 --> 00:19:45.680
that I started the problem with,
which is equal to the

00:19:45.680 --> 00:19:48.380
determinant of abcd.

00:19:48.380 --> 00:19:48.870
Right?

00:19:48.870 --> 00:19:54.340
The determinant of this is ad
minus bc, by definition.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:59.190
So your area-- this
is exciting!

00:19:59.190 --> 00:20:02.140
So the area of your
parallelogram squared is equal

00:20:02.140 --> 00:20:06.070
to the determinant of the matrix
whose column vectors

00:20:06.070 --> 00:20:08.210
construct that parallelogram.

00:20:08.210 --> 00:20:12.650
Is equal to the determinant
of your matrix squared.

00:20:12.650 --> 00:20:14.690
Or if you take the square root
of both sides, you get the

00:20:14.690 --> 00:20:19.980
area is equal to the absolute
value of the determinant of A.

00:20:19.980 --> 00:20:22.030
Which is a pretty neat
outcome, especially

00:20:22.030 --> 00:20:24.732
considering how much hairy
algebra we had to go through.

00:20:24.732 --> 00:20:28.720
Let's go back all the way over
here, go back to the drawing.

00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:34.740
So if we want to figure out the
area of this parallelogram

00:20:34.740 --> 00:20:39.610
right here, that is defined, or
that is created, by the two

00:20:39.610 --> 00:20:44.620
column vectors of a matrix, we
literally just have to find

00:20:44.620 --> 00:20:46.460
the determinant of the matrix.

00:20:46.460 --> 00:20:51.620
The area of this is equal to
the absolute value of the

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:52.630
determinant of A.

00:20:52.630 --> 00:20:54.060
And you have to do that because

00:20:54.060 --> 00:20:55.930
this might be negative.

00:20:55.930 --> 00:20:58.830
You can imagine if you swapped
these guys around, if you

00:20:58.830 --> 00:21:01.150
swapped some of the rows, this
guy would be negative, but you

00:21:01.150 --> 00:21:02.230
can 't have a negative area.

00:21:02.230 --> 00:21:04.560
And it wouldn't really change
the definition, it really

00:21:04.560 --> 00:21:05.730
wouldn't change what spanned.

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:08.960
If you switched v1 and v2,
you're still spanning the same

00:21:08.960 --> 00:21:11.470
parallelogram, you just might
get the negative of the

00:21:11.470 --> 00:21:12.770
determinant.

00:21:12.770 --> 00:21:14.640
But that is a really
neat outcome.

00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:17.240
And you know, when you first
learned determinants in

00:21:17.240 --> 00:21:20.000
school-- I mean, we learned
the first motivation for a

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:24.640
determinant was this idea of
when we take the inverse of a

00:21:24.640 --> 00:21:27.110
2 by 2, this thing shows up in
the denominator and we call

00:21:27.110 --> 00:21:28.180
that the determinant.

00:21:28.180 --> 00:21:30.470
But now there's this other
interpretation here.

00:21:30.470 --> 00:21:33.590
There's actually the area of the
parallelogram created by

00:21:33.590 --> 00:21:36.360
the column vectors
of this matrix.

